              <h2>How the West Virginia income tax calculator works</h2>
              <p>
                This tool estimates your
                <strong>West Virginia personal income tax</strong> using a
                progressive bracket system and the latest rate reductions
                enacted by the state. It is designed for:
              </p>
              <ul>
                <li>Full-year West Virginia residents</li>
                <li>Nonresidents with West Virginia–source income</li>
                <li>
                  Part-year residents who moved into or out of WV during the
                  year
                </li>
              </ul>

              <h3>Step 1 – Start with your annual taxable income</h3>
              <p>
                Enter your <strong>annual taxable income</strong> in the
                calculator. This should be your income that is potentially
                taxable by West Virginia after federal adjustments (for example,
                pre-tax retirement contributions or HSA contributions).
              </p>

              <h3>Step 2 – Adjust for residency and WV-source income</h3>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  <strong>Resident</strong> – Generally taxed on all income,
                  regardless of where it is earned.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Nonresident</strong> – Taxed only on
                  <strong>West Virginia–source income</strong> (for example,
                  wages earned in WV).
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Part-year resident</strong> – Taxed as a resident for
                  the part of the year you lived in WV, and as a nonresident for
                  the rest.
                </li>
              </ul>
              <p>
                Use the <strong>“WV-source income share”</strong> slider to
                approximate what portion of your total income is taxable in West
                Virginia. The calculator multiplies:
              </p>
              <div class="formula-box">
                <code
                  >WV-source income = Annual income × (WV-source share ÷
                  100)</code
                >
              </div>

              <h3>Step 3 – Subtract deductions</h3>
              <p>
                The calculator subtracts three types of deductions before
                applying the tax brackets:
              </p>
              <ol>
                <li>
                  <strong>Pre-tax 401(k)/IRA contributions</strong> – Amount you
                  enter in the “Pre-tax 401(k)/traditional IRA” field.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Other WV deductions</strong> – Any additional
                  deductions you expect to claim on your WV return.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong>Estimated WV standard deduction</strong> – If the
                  checkbox is enabled, we apply a filing-status-based standard
                  deduction approximation.
                </li>
              </ol>
              <p>The formula for adjusted WV taxable income is:</p>
              <div class="formula-box">
                <code>
                  Adjusted WV taxable income = max(0, WV-source income − pre-tax
                  retirement − other deductions − standard deduction)
                </code>
              </div>

              <h3>Step 4 – Apply West Virginia tax brackets</h3>
              <p>
                West Virginia uses a <strong>progressive tax system</strong>.
                Your income is split into ranges (brackets), and each range is
                taxed at a different rate. The calculator:
              </p>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  Determines which brackets your adjusted income falls into.
                </li>
                <li>Applies the corresponding rate to each slice of income.</li>
                <li>Sums the results to get your total WV income tax.</li>
              </ul>
              <p>Your <strong>effective tax rate</strong> is then:</p>
              <div class="formula-box">
                <code
                  >Effective WV tax rate = (WV tax ÷ Annual income) × 100%</code
                >
              </div>

